@end menu

@node Editing a note
@subsection Editing a note

@enumerate
@item
Edit the org file.
@item
Export with @samp{C-c C-e H H} (current subtree).
@item
Hugo live reload picks it up.
@end enumerate

@node Editing a quote
@subsection Editing a quote

@enumerate
@item
Edit the @samp{:public:} subtree in the bibliographic note.
@item
Export with @samp{C-c C-e H A} (all subtrees).
@item
Hugo live reload picks it up.
@end enumerate

@node Org-transclusion support
@subsection Org-transclusion support

Org files may contain @samp{#+transclude:} directives (from @samp{org-transclusion.el}) that pull content from other files.  Both export paths handle these automatically:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Interactive export} (@samp{C-c C-e H H}): advice on @code{org-hugo-export-wim-to-md} temporarily expands all transclusions before export and removes them afterward, so the source buffer is not permanently modified.  This requires @samp{org-transclusion} to be installed but does not require @code{org-transclusion-mode} to be active.

@item
@strong{Batch export} (@samp{M-x stafforini-export-all-notes}): the batch pipeline calls @code{org-transclusion-add-all} per file via @code{export--expand-transclusions} in @samp{export-common.el}.
@end itemize

@node Targeted updates
@section Targeted updates

Use these when you've changed a specific upstream source @emph{without} editing org content. Each command updates only what it needs to.

@itemize
@item
@strong{Changed a Bib@TeX{} entry} → @samp{M-x stafforini-update-works}. Regenerates work pages from Bib@TeX{} data. Auto-restarts the server (Hugo doesn't track shortcode cross-references, so live reload won't propagate Bib@TeX{} changes to citing pages).

@item
@strong{Changed links between notes} → @samp{M-x stafforini-update-backlinks}. Regenerates backlink data from the org-roam database. Auto-restarts the server.

@item
@strong{Created a new org note file} → @samp{M-x stafforini-prepare-notes}. Adds ox-hugo metadata (@samp{:EXPORT_FILE_NAME:}, @samp{:EXPORT_HUGO_SECTION:}, etc.) to new files that don't have it yet. Run @emph{before} exporting.

@item
@strong{Added or changed PDFs} → @samp{M-x stafforini-process-pdfs}. Strips annotations and generates first-page thumbnails.

@item
@strong{Search index out of date} → @samp{M-x stafforini-rebuild-search-index}. Rebuilds the Pagefind index. Useful after content changes when you want to test search locally without a full rebuild.
@end itemize

@node Batch export
@section Batch export

Use these after mass edits, migrations, or whenever you want to ensure everything is in sync. Each export command handles its full pipeline automatically — no need to run intermediate scripts.

@itemize
@item
@samp{M-x stafforini-export-all-notes} — exports all org notes, then runs inject-lastmod, generate-backlinks, and generate-citing-notes.
@item
@samp{M-x stafforini-export-all-quotes} — generates the ID→slug map, exports all org quotes, then generates work pages and topic pages. Tag injection (from @samp{:TOPICS:} properties) runs as part of both pipelines.
@end itemize

After batch exporting, restart the server with @samp{M-x stafforini-start-server} to pick up all changes.

@node Full rebuild
@section Full rebuild

@samp{M-x stafforini-full-rebuild} — runs the entire pipeline from scratch (7 steps: prepare notes → export notes → export quotes → process PDFs → clean public contents → hugo build → pagefind index). Use after major structural changes, or as a final check before deploying. Overkill for day-to-day work. The clean step preserves symlinks (e.g. nosync) by deleting contents rather than the directory itself.

@node Deploying
@section Deploying

@enumerate
@item
Run the needed export/update steps.
@item
@samp{M-x stafforini-start-server} to verify locally.
@item
@samp{M-x stafforini-deploy}.
@end enumerate

With a prefix argument (@samp{C-u M-x stafforini-deploy}, or @samp{C-u D} in the menu), the command runs a quick deploy that skips content export, data regeneration, and PDF processing (passing @samp{--quick} to @samp{deploy.sh}).  Use this when only templates, styles, or static assets changed after a recent full export.

@samp{M-x stafforini-deploy-fast-note} (or @samp{f} in the menu) runs the fast note deploy path (passing @samp{--fast-note} to @samp{deploy.sh}). Use this only for minor already-exported note body edits. It preserves the existing @samp{public/} snapshot and Pagefind search index, so use the normal deploy path for slug, date, tag, citation, link, template, quote, work-page, PDF, new-note, or deleted-note changes.

@node Automatic behaviors
@section Automatic behaviors

These run silently as you work on note org files. No command to
invoke — configure via @samp{M-x customize-group RET stafforini}.

