@node @samp{#+lastmod} keyword stamping
@subsection @samp{#+lastmod:} keyword stamping

Saving an org file under @samp{stafforini-lastmod-directories} (by default
@samp{~/My Drive/notes/} and @samp{~/My Drive/bibliographic-notes/}) updates a
file-level @samp{#+lastmod:} keyword with the current timestamp. The
stafforini.com pipeline's @samp{inject-lastmod.py} reads this keyword as
the authoritative last-modification date, in preference to git
history.

The hook is a no-op in batch mode (@samp{emacs --script}, etc.) and for
any command listed in @samp{stafforini-lastmod-skip-commands}. Extend that
list to silence sweeping interactive operations (bulk property
migrations, @samp{dired-do-query-replace-regexp}, etc.) that modify many
files without representing real content edits.

@node Duplicate @samp{PROPERTIES} drawer warning
@subsection Duplicate @samp{PROPERTIES} drawer warning

After saving an org file, a warning is displayed if the first heading
has two consecutive @samp{:PROPERTIES:} drawers — a known corruption mode
caused by an intermittent ox-hugo bug.

@node Server management
@section Server management

@itemize
@item
@samp{M-x stafforini-start-server} — starts (or restarts) the Hugo dev server. Always kills any existing server first to ensure a fresh build.
@item
@samp{M-x stafforini-stop-server} — stops the server.
@end itemize

@menu
* When to restart the server::
@end menu

@node When to restart the server
@subsection When to restart the server

@itemize
@item
@strong{Same page changed} → live reload works, no restart needed.
@item
@strong{Change affects other pages} (Bib@TeX{}, backlinks, work pages, citing-notes) → restart with @samp{M-x stafforini-start-server}. The standalone @samp{update-works} and @samp{update-backlinks} commands do this automatically.
@end itemize

